<hl>
<seg id=1> Zhejiang Wenzhou is working hard on repairing the dam that was damaged by number 17 Typhoon. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Wenzhou, September 1st, by Hongwei Hu, Yuntin Xie- The news from Wenshou City Flooding and Drought Control Headquarters said that the city is working hard to repair the damage to the irrigation dam that was destroyed by Typhoon number 17. </seg>
<seg id=3> Up to August 30th, the city has been using as many as 158,300 workers each day, with a total of 936,500 workers helping so far.  They have already filled 73,000 square meters with sand and stones. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The number 17 typhoon hit Wenshou city directly, damaging the 862 kilometers of the dam. Inside the damaged area, 357 kilometers of the dam were totally destroyed. </seg>
<seg id=5> According to the Chinese Lunar calendar, August the 3rd and the 15th are the most likely days for flooding, so new Typhoons and storms could be near any time.  The situation is dangerous. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Wenzhou residents currently are working hard to protect their properties and repair the dam. </seg>
<seg id=7> 991 damaged areas of the dam have already been repaired.  Lots of bags and other needed supplies have already been sent from other cities in Zhejiang. </seg>
<seg id=8> It is predicted that, before the arrival of August 3rd, the most severely damaged portions of the dam will be at least temporarily repaired with walls of soil. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> It is told that Wenzhou city government has already made a strategic plan from this winter to next spring, the whole city will begin a new upsurge of building irrigation works. </seg>
</p>
